title: 13/10:22 EST Initial Flood Warning for the Norman River
text:
Bureau Home > Australia > Queensland > Warnings Summary >   Gulf Rivers   Gulf Rivers IDQ20875   Meteorology, Queensland Initial   Norman River Issued at 10:22   2017 
Flood Warning Number: 1 
Minor flooding is occurring in the Norman River catchment. 
Rainfall totals up to 90 mm have been recorded in the Norman River catchment in the 24 hours to 9:00 am Friday. Norman River: Minor flooding is rising at Yappar River, Glenore Weir and Lower Walker Creek in the Norman River catchment. Flood Safety Advice: 
Remember: If it's flooded, forget it. For flood emergency assistance contact the SES on 132 500. For life threatening emergencies, call Triple Zero (000) immediately. 
Current emergency information is available at www.qld.gov.au/alerts Next Issue: 
The next warning will be issued by 10:30 am EST on Saturday 14 January 2017. Latest River Heights:
